\f0\fs14 \cf2 //I'm attaching a file of some code to get you started on the latest \'ca
\f1 \uc0\u8232 
\f0 assignment. \'caIt demonstrates a Routine that creates a cloud of \'ca
\f1 \uc0\u8232 
\f0 granular sine-wave synths, and randomizes a few its parameters. \'caIt \'ca
\f1 \uc0\u8232 
\f0 also creates a GUI window with a button to start a cloud, and a \'ca
\f1 \uc0\u8232 
\f0 single SCRangeSlider for adjusting the range that frequencies are \'ca
\f1 \uc0\u8232 
\f0 chosen from. \'caIt's up to you to add other ones to control other \'ca
\f1 \uc0\u8232 
\f0 parameters. \'ca Note also that the parameters that are used in creating \'ca
\f1 \uc0\u8232 
\f0 a cloud will stay fixed during the generation of all events in the \'ca
\f1 \uc0\u8232 
\f0 cloud -- this allows you to edit the parameters before starting \'ca
\f1 \uc0\u8232 
\f0 another cloud, at which point the new cloud will use the new \'ca
\f1 \uc0\u8232 
\f0 parameter settings, but the old one continues using the same ones as \'ca
\f1 \uc0\u8232 
\f0 before. \'caIf you want the parameters to change during the generation \'ca
\f1 \uc0\u8232 
\f0 of the cloud, it's up to you to find another way to do that!
\f1 \uc0\u8232 \u8232 
\f0 If you need more challenges, look to the examples in the Granular \'ca
\f1 \uc0\u8232 
\f0 Synthesis code file for additional features to add. \'caHave fun!
